    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Add 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
