    {
      "instruction": "<p>Press each dough ball<strong> </strong>in the centre and gently push outwards with your fingertips, leaving the rim of the pizza untouched to form a <strong>crust </strong>(don't worry if the dough rips, just stick it back together and carry on!)</p><p>Tip: Dust with extra sprinkles of flour as you go to stop it sticking!</p><p>Keep going until your base is slightly smaller than a side plate (you will make them bigger in the pan!) – these are your <strong>pizza bases</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan <span class=\"text-danger\">[or 2]</span> (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
