        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Repeat this process for the remaining pizza base<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Tip: Make sure the pizzas don't overlap on the tray to avoid raw dough!</p><p>Top them with the <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>torn mozzarella </strong>and <strong>pepperoni slices </strong>then scatter over the<strong> quick-pickled chillies </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped olives </strong>and <strong>basil leaves</strong></p><p>Drizzle the crusts with <strong>olive oil</strong>, then put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span><strong> </strong>in the oven for 12-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the crust has puffed up and browned</p>",
